    public class Constructor
extends BodyMethodDeclaration
    MethodDeclaration extension that represents the declaration of a Constructor node type. See decodeStatement(Node, String, Location, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

        public java.lang.StringBuilder generateCSourcePrototype(java.lang.StringBuilder builder)
        Description copied from class: MethodDeclaration
        Generate the C prototype for the method header.

         public void test()
 {
        ...
 }
        will output as "static void test();"

      • decodeStatement

        public static Constructor decodeStatement(Node parent,
                                          java.lang.String statement,
                                          Location location,
                                          boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into a Constructor instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null. A constructor must have the same name as the class that it is within. Constructors also do not have a return value.

        Example inputs include:
        • public ClassName()
        • private ClassName(int numChildren, String name)
        • public ClassName(Node parent, Location location)
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a Constructor instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a Constructor.

      • interactWord

        public void interactWord(java.lang.String word,
                         int wordNumber,
                         Bounds bounds,
                         int numWords,
                         java.lang.String leftDelimiter,
                         java.lang.String rightDelimiter,
                         Node.ExtraData extra)
        Description copied from class: Node
        Method that is to be overridden. Whenever the iterateWords(String) method is called, this method will be called with the specific word and the number (order) the word came in the statement.
        Overrides:
        interactWord in class NovaMethodDeclaration
        Parameters:
        word - The word that was found.
        wordNumber - The index of the word on a word-by-word basis.
        bounds - The bounds of the word that was found.
        numWords - The number of words that were parsed.
        leftDelimiter - The text that is between the previous word and the current word.
        rightDelimiter - The text that is between the current word and the next word.
        extra - The extra data that may or may not be needed for the interactWord() methods.
        See Also:
        Node.interactWord(java.lang.String, int, net.fathomsoft.nova.util.Bounds, int, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Node.ExtraData)
